Product: SharePoint Server Subscription Edition on-prem

Issue:
Production SharePoint SE document libraries do not show the expected modern relative upload time after a new file is uploaded. Stage shows the expected behaviour, e.g. “uploaded a few seconds ago / a minute ago”. Production immediately renders a fixed/current date instead.

Important:
The item data itself is correct. This appears to be a modern UI/date rendering issue, not a Created field/storage/timezone issue.

Environment:
- SharePoint Server Subscription Edition on-prem
- Separate Stage and Production farms
- Stage and Production appear to have the same patch/build level in Central Administration
- Web application/list experience settings appear the same
- Issue occurs in existing and newly created libraries in Production

Checks already completed:
1. Server date/time is correct on both Stage and Production.
2. Windows timezone is correct on both Stage and Production.
3. SharePoint site regional timezone is correct.
4. Production site LocaleId is 3081, English Australia.
5. Site language shows 1033.
6. Language Settings page has been compared between Stage and Production and matches.
7. Personal regional settings have been checked and both are set to follow web settings.
8. Created field raw value has been checked with PowerShell and is correct.
9. Created field settings compared:
   - FriendlyDisplayFormat = 0
   - DisplayFormat = 1
10. Temporarily forcing Created FriendlyDisplayFormat to Relative changed the display to weekday-style text, but did not restore the expected “uploaded a few seconds ago” behaviour. This was reverted.
11. ListExperienceOptions was Auto. Temporarily forcing NewExperience did not resolve the issue. This was reverted.
12. Web application list experience settings were compared and appear the same.
13. New libraries in Production show the same issue.

Requested investigation:
Please investigate why Production is not rendering modern document library relative dates/times correctly, despite the Created value, timezone, locale, language settings, personal regional settings, patch level, and list experience settings appearing correct.

I suspect this is related to modern list/library client-side rendering, culture/resource files, cached/stale modern UI assets, WFE/resource deployment, PSConfig/static resource state, or a SharePoint SE rendering bug/regression.
